          <div class="point"><h4><span class="point-num">2.</span>Supports acetylcholine production.</h4><p>Acetylcholine is the neurotransmitter behind focus, attention, learning, and memory. Every time you concentrate, your brain spends acetylcholine. Alpha-GPC is studied for its role in supporting healthy levels.</p></div>
          <div class="point"><h4><span class="point-num">3.</span>Reaches the brain quickly.</h4><p>Alpha-GPC is absorbed and reaches neural tissue within about 30 minutes, faster than most choline sources. This is why it's studied as an acute cognitive support compound.</p></div>
          <div class="point"><h4><span class="point-num">4.</span>Supports neural cell membranes.</h4><p>Alpha-GPC contributes to phosphatidylcholine, a structural component of brain cell membranes. These membranes play a role in healthy cognitive function.</p></div>
